namePublicLong: Brancott Estate Pinot Grigio 750mL Bottle

namePublicLong: Campo Viejo The Red Blend Red Wine, 750 mL Bottle, 13.5% ABV

namePublicLong: Campo Viejo The Vibrant Blend White Wine, 750 mL Bottle, 12% ABV

The nose is exotic fruit like mango, passionfruit, and pineapple, along with floral notes and freshly cut grass. To finish it presents a fresh, perfumed mouth, very long, leaving us the memory of the Moscato fruit.

namePublicLong: Brancott Estate Pinot Noir 750mL Bottle
namePublicShort: Brancott Estate Pinot Noir opens with bundles of red fruit, spice and vanilla aromas. The palate is sweetly-fruited, with strawberry, ripe red cherry and plum on an elegant, medium weight body. The tannins are supple and integrated, and the red fruit and spicy oak flavors persist on the finish.

Riva De La Rosa Gavi Italian White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Riva de la Rosa Gavi DOCG is crafted from the Cortese grape cultivated in the sun-drenched Terre del Gavi hills, nestled on the border between Monferrato and Liguria. Cool breezes from the Ligurian Sea and abundant sunlight greatly influence the vineyard's microclimate, creating an ideal environment to cultivate exceptional Gavi DOCG vineyards. This distinctive combination of microclimate and clay marl soils results in a well-balanced wine, boasting an expressive bouquet of floral and vibrant citrus notes.

namePublicLong: Windstream Monterey Pinot Noir Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Inspired by the ever-present winds and fog of the Santa Lucia Highlands, Windstream embodies the best wines grown in the Riboli Family’s Sarmento Vineyard estate. This cool climate is ideal for crafting Pinot Noir and Chardonnay wines that reflect the true terroir of this small but mighty winegrowing appellation in Monterey.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Paso Robles Syrah Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: San Simeon Syrah Red Wine is fermented and aged in our state-of-the-art winery. Our Syrah reveals deep color, round tannins, and plush mouthfeel with intense flavors and aromas, such as boysenberry, ripe plum, and pomegranate. The lengthy finish shows vanilla, oak spice and cinnamon nuances from barrel-aging. Pairs well with Pepper Steak, Lamb Tagine, & Soublaki.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Berry Semi-Sweet Rose Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Berry Semi-Sweet Rose Wine is a proprietary blend of several Italian red grape varietals including Brachetto. The wine is then combined with all-natural flavors of ripe strawberry, blackberry and red berry to create a delicious and refreshing experience. Serve chilled by the glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all-natural, fruit-forward cocktail. 90-point Gold Medal winner at the Los Angeles International Wine Competition.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Paso Robles Sauvignon Blanc White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: San Simeon Sauvignon Blanc White Wine was sourced from two vineyards from the relatively new Creston District AVA in Paso Robles. Intense aromas of white flowers and honey with fresh, grassy notes on the nose of this bright, well-balanced wine. The rich palate shows classic Sauvignon Blanc flavors of bright citrus, pear, and lime zest along with a slight hint of minerality. With nice acidity and a long, soft finish, this is an ideal wine to enjoy on a warm summer afternoon.

namePublicLong: Santo Moscato d'Asti DOCG White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Santo Moscato d’Asti DOCG is a naturally effervescent wine made from the highest quality level Moscato grapes. The juice is fermented in Charmat-style, pressurized tanks. As the alcohol is created, so is the carbonation. Once the desired sweetness is achieved, the wine is centrifuged and bottled. Our Moscato d’Asti has a delicate and aromatic nose, sometimes presenting notes of sage and bursting with tropical and citrus notes on the palate. Perfect with desserts and fruit.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Paso Robles Stormwatch Red Blend Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: San Simeon Stormwatch Red Wine is a Bordeaux-style red blend in the truest sense, combining the five noble grape varietals including Cabernet Sauvignon, Petit Verdot, Merlot, Cabernet Franc and Malbec. Harvested in small lots and kept separate through fermentation and aging, the components of San Simeon Stormwatch matured for 18 months in 89% French oak barrels. The black-violet hue of this complex wine is a tip off to the aromas of blackberries, black currants and dark plum that arise from the glass. The powerful mid-palate reveals similar fruit flavors joined by dark chocolate and vanilla with a touch of thyme. Earth, oak and spice notes add to the appeal of this well-balanced red wine, which ends in a persistent finish and warm, silky tannins.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Imperiale Brachetto d'Acqui Sparkling Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Imperiale Brachetto D’Acqui Sparkling Red Wine is one of the world’s most unique, aromatic, semi-sweet, sparkling red wines. The prized grapes are selected from specific family-cultivated vineyards in and around the commune of Asti. The northwestern province of Piedmonte is home to Stella Rosa Imperiale Brachetto d’Acqui, one of the world’s most unique, aromatic, semi-sweet, sparkling red wines. The prized grapes are selected from specific family-cultivated vineyards in and around the commune of Asti.

namePublicLong: San Antonio Fruit Farm Blackberry Orange Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Fruit Farm Blackberry Orange is the perfect wine to set the mood for an intimate movie night, late night grub sesh, or dinner party. It’s handcrafted with Brachetto-Malvasia grapes harvested from our northern hillside vineyards in Piedmont, Italy. Blackberry-orange juice, made using all natural whole fruits, is then blended to create a delicate yet rich flavor profile. You can’t go wrong with this bold flavor combo and rich color that still brings a light twist of fun to any event. Naturally crafted with two fruits. Serve chilled with light snacks.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Red Semi-Sweet Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Red Semi-Sweet Red Wine is a proprietary blend of several red grape varietals. The wine is combined with natural flavors of ripe raspberry, wild strawberry, and red plum. namePublicLong: Maddalena Paso Robles Rose Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Maddalena Rose is the Grenache varietal, grown in our Stefano Vineyard in the renowned El Pomar AVA in Paso Robles, California. Light and bright with a pale pink hue, our Maddalena Rose shows notes of fresh strawberry, melon, and yellow peach graced with accents of scented rose. With bright acidity and a zesty attack, this is a fresh, well-balanced wine, fruity but pleasantly dry, with a nice spicy finish.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Imperiale Orange Moscato DOCG Sparkling White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: The northeastern province of Veneto is home to Stella Rosa Imperiale Orange Moscato, one of the world’s most unique, semi-sweet sparkling Moscatos. The prized Fior D’Arancio Moscato grapes are selected from specific family cultivated vineyards in Colli Euganei. . Its natural acidity and low pH strike the perfect balance with the wine’s inherent sweetness. It is not cloying or heavy. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

Made from 100% natural grapes and fermented naturally. Serve slightly chilled.

namePublicLong: Maddalena Paso Robles Merlot Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Maddalena Merlot offers aromas of ripe fruit and oak spice with hints of vanilla and anise. Ripe fruit flavors include bright plum and raspberry. Fruit flavors greet the palate and soft tannins frame the fresh texture that coats the mouth. Maddalena Merlot is extremely food friendly, our Merlot pairs well with a range of dishes. Sustainability is our top priority. Our Paso Robles and Monterey vineyards are certified sustainable by CSWA.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Paso Robles Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine 375 ml
namePublicShort: San Simeon Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine was aged in a selection of 78% new French and American Oak barrels.This is a high intensity Cabernet with bright color and robust flavors of blackberry, plum and black cherry. This is a deeply satisfying Cabernet with a long, round finish. Sustainability is a top priority at San Simeon. Our Paso Robles Vineyards are certified sustainable by the rigorous California Sustainable Wine Alliance (CSWA).

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Platinum French Vanilla Semi-Sweet White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Platinum French Vanilla is crafted in the small village of Santo Stefano Belbo. The Riboli Family has created this special blend of several aromatic grape varietals including Moscato Canelli. The Riboli family uses this technique to capture the fresh flavors of green apple, fragrant vanilla, and citrusy elderflower. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all-natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Imperiale Moscato Sparkling White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Imperiale Moscato Sparkling White Wine is one of the world’s highest-quality “super moscatos.” The prized Moscato grapes are selected from specific family-cultivated vineyards in the communes of Asti, Alessandria, and Cuneo.  Its natural acidity and low pH strike the perfect balance with the wine’s inherent sweetness. It is not cloying or heavy. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: Maddalena Monterey Pinot Grigio White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Our Maddalena Pinot Grigio is 100% Pinot Grigio and was farmed from our Rancho Soledad Vineyard in Monterey, so named for the nearby Soledad Mission founded in 1791. With its close proximity to the Pacific Ocean, the Monterey appellation has a classic cool climate with morning fog and afternoon breezes; here, grapes develop flavor slowly and fully while preserving precious natural acidity. Rancho Soledad’s sandy loam soils are derived from decomposed granite, imparting a slight minerality to its wines. The 2021 growing season was long and cool, even for Monterey, yielding fruit that showed refined phenolic development. We harvested the fruit for this Pinot Grigio in one pass on September 23rd. This is a dry, light bodied wine that reveals notes of baking spice and honeysuckle on a persistent finish. We are proud that our Paso Robles and Monterey vineyards are certified sustainable by CSWA.

namePublicLong: Riva De La Rosa Vermentino Italian White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Riva de la Rosa’s Vermentino IGT, a varietal often referred to as "the wine of the sun and sea". Grown predominantly along the sun-kissed coastal vineyards of the Mediterranean, especially in Tuscany and the island of Sardinia. This complex and light-bodied white wine thrives amidst warm sunlight and refreshing sea breezes. Riva de la Rosa Vermentino IGT captures the essence of the sea with its pronounced salinity, leading to a captivating phenolic finish, making it an ideal companion for herb-infused dishes and delicate pastas.

namePublicLong: Riva De La Rosa Frascati Italian White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Riva De La Rosa Frascati DOC is produced in the Tenuta Pietra Porzia family vineyard, situated in the heart of the production zone, offering a spectacular view of Rome and Castelli Romani. Frascati, renowned as "the wine of kings and popes" and “the golden wine of the Romans” has flourished in Rome for over two thousand years. Produced predominantly from the Malvasia grape, the rich volcanic soil, plentiful sunshine, and cool breezes provides an ideal climate suited for this varietal. With its bright fruity flavors, Riva de la Rosa' Frascati DOC serves as a wonderful aperitif as well as an excellent companion to light dishes.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Lime Chili White Wine 750ml
namePublicShort: Spice up your next party with our new Stella Rosa Lime Chili Wine. This semi-sweet, semi-sparkling wine is made with a proprietary blend of primarily the Moscato D’Asti grape with natural flavors of fresh lime and spicy chili. This bold flavor is sure to impress. Serve chilled, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit in a cocktail.

namePublicLong: Opaque Paso Robles Tannat Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Originally from Basque country on the border between France and Spain, Tannat is named from a French word referring to “tanned” or its deep color. We were so impressed by this wine that we bottled it without any blending. After aging in French oak barrels for 18 months, our wine reveals concentrated black plum and blueberry aromas with a touch of dry earth and leather. On the palate, it is dense with dark fruit flavors and a peppery spice with structured tannins that provide texture and depth with a lengthy finish.

namePublicLong: Santo Signature Cuvee Sparkling White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Santo Signature Cuvee Italian Sparkling Wine is comprised of 100% Glera grapes that come from our winery in Veneto. Our winery is within the small village of Valdobbiadene, the traditional home of Prosecco. The winery first started producing sparkling wine in 1861. The history of sparkling wine in the Veneto is rich and connected with food and culture throughout Northern Italy.

namePublicLong: San Antonio Fruit Farm Cherry Lime Rose Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: To handcraft San Antonio Fruit Farm Cherry Lime Rosé wine, White Moscato and Brachetto grapes are harvested from our northern hillside vineyards in Piedmont, Italy. Cherry Lime fruit juice is then blended to create a delicate yet rich flavor profile. Whether at a family reunion or at an outdoor event, this wonderfully light, fruity, and sparkling beverage will complement any moment. Naturally crafted with two fruits. Serve chilled with light snacks.

namePublicLong: San Antonio Fruit Farm Strawberry Guava Rose Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Fresh, light, and always more fun to drink together, San Antonio Fruit Farm Strawberry Guava Rosé Wine is a semi-sweet wine that pairs well with bubbly conversation, afternoon picnics, and catching up with old friends without missing a beat. It’s handcrafted with Brachetto-Malvasia grapes harvested from our northern hillside vineyards in Piedmont, Italy. Strawberry-Guava juice, made using all natural whole fruits, is then blended to create a delicate yet rich flavor profile. Naturally crafted with two fruits. Serve chilled with light snacks.

namePublicLong: The Champion New Zealand Sauvignon Blanc White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: To achieve The Champion Sauvignon Blanc White Wine, we utilize a small artisan vineyard located on the South Island in Marlborough, New Zealand. The resulting flavors are intensely tropical in contrast to the conventional, leaner 'green herbaceous' commonly represented styles. A crisp wine boasting the fruit-forward flavors of passionfruit, gooseberry, and pink grapefruit. Intense tropical flavors are balanced with acidity for versatility. Showcased with a lively and juicy brightness and a pleasant, lingering finish.

namePublicLong: Opaque Paso Robles Darkness Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Opaque Darkness Red Wine refers to the dark, inky, impenetrable color of our family’s proprietary blend. We were so impressed by the Zinfandel, Syrah, Cabernet Sauvignon, Petite Sirah, Petit Verdot, and Malbec grapes from our estate vineyards in Paso Robles, that we reserved them for this special blend. After aging in French and American barrels for 15 months, our hand-crafted artisan blend reveals ripe flavors of raspberry and blackberry with notes of spice and vanilla. Enjoy the darkness!

namePublicLong: Opaque Paso Robles Petit Verdot Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Opaque Petit Verdot lives up to its namesake, with a deep, dark red color that promises a profoundly rich and satisfying wine. Blackberry, currant and black plum dominate the palate, supported by mocha and vanilla crème. Aged for 18 months in French and American oak barrels - 79% new – this Petit Verdot shows great concentration and texture, spicy richness, and tannins that are long, soft and round. The wine has a long, powerful finish and the structure to age beautifully for a decade at least.

namePublicLong: Les Glories Sancerre Blanc White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Les Glories Sancerre Blanc White Wine features a golden yellow color with green tints. Fruity citrus nose. A pure Sancerre with incredible freshness and minerality. It stands in contrast to some productions which tend toward richer, heavier wines often with residual sugar. It has a good depth, lovely, citrus fruit, and a classic flintiness on the nose and palate. We seek expression of this fine and delicate mouthfeel, emphasizing harmony to this beautiful Sancerre expression!  Best served at 10° - 11° C. Will best accompany laminated salmon and other fishes in sauce, grilled fish, Crustaceans, and goat cheese. Aperitif.

namePublicLong: Windstream Monterey Chardonnay White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Windstream Chardonnay is a single vineyard wine from the Sarmento Vineyard, located within the prestigious Santa Lucia Highlands appellation of Monterey County. This Chardonnay was 100% barrel fermented in small French oak barrels – 94% new – with 64% of the wine undergoing a secondary malolactic fermentation. Light gold in color, the wine rushes in with potent fruit notes of pineapple and grapefruit unfolding to reveal dried fruits, nuts, brown sugar, and spice. With a full body and lovely texture, this Chardonnay provides a rich, mouth-filling experience that stays well-balanced due to natural acidity. Coating tannins make for a long finish that lingers with hints of mineral, vanilla, and almonds

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Lemon Lime Semi-Sweet White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort:
Stella Rosa Lemon Lime Semi-Sweet White Wine 750 ml is a proprietary blend produced primarily from the Moscato grape with various other varietals. The addition of a custom, proprietary blend of natural lemon and lime flavors makes this truly unique. 
The grapes are harvested, pressed, centrifuged, and then held cold as juice at 28 degrees Fahrenheit. The juice is fermented at various intervals throughout the year allowing the wine to remain fresh and delicate. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all-natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Monterey Chardonnay White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: San Simeon Chardonnay comes only from the best lots that our estate vineyards have to offer. San Simeon Chardonnay is a rich, mouth-filling wine with ripe, tropical fruit flavors with complements of citrus and pear. This structured and well-balanced wine shows a lengthy finish with potential to age. Extremely food friendly, our San Simeon Chardonnay pairs well with a range of dishes. From poultry and pasta to seafood and salads, our Chardonnay shines.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Paso Robles Merlot Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: San Simeon Merlot blends grapes from two estate vineyards in Paso Robles, including Maddalena and Riboli Creston. With warm daytime temperatures and cool evenings, the climate in both vineyards is excellent for nurturing mature Merlot vines. A cool season gave grapes ample time on the vine to develop color, flavor, acid and tannin. The wine is bright red in color, with a shiny hue and pleasant aromas of red fruits, blueberries and cassis. With nice acidity and a touch of spice, this is a well-integrated Merlot that finishes with soft, round tannins. Our Paso Robles and Monterey vineyards are certified sustainable by CSWA.

namePublicLong: Opaque Paso Robles Malbec Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Opaque Malbec was grown in our Maddalena Vineyard in the prestigious El Pomar AVA of Paso Robles. At Maddalena, steep hillsides of Linne-Calodo calcareous soils derived from ancient seabeds force the vines to struggle to absorb nutrients, creating concentrated grapes and wines with a unique mineral character. Fermented in stainless steel and aged in 70% new French oak barrels, this is a classic Malbec with deep purple/red color and lovely aromatics of violets and ripe blueberries. With nice acidity and great texture, this is a supremely well-balanced wine with a soft, round midpalate, silky tannins and a long persistent finish.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Pinot Grigio Italian White Wine 375 ml
namePublicShort: Our new Stella Rosa Pinot Grigio was born from rich grapes grown in the beautiful valleys near the Trentino mountains. Straw-yellow colored, this Pinot Grigio is crisp and dry, with flavors of honey, green apple and pear, created to be served chilled and at 12% ABV. Perfect with appetizers, grilled chicken, and salads.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Paso Robles Petite Sirah Red Wine 750 ml

Aging in French and American oak barrels contributes notes of vanilla and oak spice. The mouthfeel is jammy and full-bodied. Enjoy San Simeon Petite Sirah with Oso Buco or short ribs! Sustainability is our top priority. Our Paso Robles and Monterey vineyards are certified sustainable by CSWA.

Enjoy this wine after dinner with dried fruits, nuts, and all types of chocolate. Try it with dried apricots and cherries, chocolate-covered strawberries, and anything chocolate. Pair it with pecan pie and all of your favorite desserts. Made with 4 Selections of Port Wine Infused with 100% natural chocolate and cocoa.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Paso Robles Grenache Rose Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Our San Simeon Paso Robles Grenache Rosé Wine is 100% Grenache from our Stefano Vineyard in the celebrated El Pomar appellation in Paso Robles. With a rich, round body and moderately high acidity, this is a beautifully structured wine with a long, satisfying finish. namePublicLong: Riva De La Rosa Sauvignon Blanc DOC Italian White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Riva De La Rosa Sauvignon Blanc DOC is produced in the Friuili DOC because it is ideal for growing Sauvignon Blanc due of the proximity of the Alps to the North and a sea breeze that blows in from the Adriatic Sea to their South. This prestigious winemaking region has a history of viticulture dating back to the Romans, known for cultivating exceptional wines. Our Sauvignon Blanc is cold fermented at a controlled temperature of 12-14°C in stainless steel tanks. The alluvial plain and sandy soils of the Friuli region influence the flavor of this grape, making it a unique and refreshing Sauvignon Blanc.

namePublicLong: San Antonio Port Red Wine 3L
namePublicShort: San Antonio Port has a ruby color with tawny hues and ripe flavors of raisin and prune. San Antonio is one of the last wineries to specialize in the production of fine dessert wines. namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Gold V.S. Prosecco Sparkling White Wine DOC 750ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Gold V.S. Prosecco D.O.C starts with specially selected grapes grown in the beautiful vineyards of the Veneto region in Italy. The blend undergoes a very long fermentation to yield a richer, more elegant Prosecco with more pronounced character. The bottles are hand wrapped with a beautiful, shiny gold finish making it perfect for gifting.  Imported from Italy.

namePublicLong: Santo Rose Semi-Sparkling Rose Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Santo Rosé Semi-Sparkling Rosé Wine is a blend of 55% Trebbiano, 40% Glera, 5% Barbera from Piedmont, Italy. It is produced with light skin contact and gentle pressing resulting in a crystal-clear, pink colour. The nose is vibrant with layered aromas of cherry, strawberry, rose blossom and bubble gum. The bright acidity brings crispiness on the palate, beautifully balancing the sugars. Delightful with appetizers, cheese, and fish.

namePublicLong: Highlands 41 Monterey Pinot Noir Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Highlands 41 Pinot Noir is crafted from 100% estate-owned fruit grown in the heart of Monterey County. Each bottle of Highlands 41 Pinot Noir takes you on an adventure. Our Paso Robles and Monterey vineyards are certified sustainable by CSWA.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Imperiale Asti DOCG Sparkling White Wine 750 ml

Grown from Moscato Bianco grapes on the steep hills of Piedmont, Asti has a natural sweetness and a floral bouquet of elegance, with notes of honey and wisteria and a delicate, balanced and aromatic taste. Its natural sweetness and lively effervescence make it perfect for mixing in cocktails to enhance fruit flavor or as a standalone aperitif.

namePublicLong: Riboli Family Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: The Riboli Family has farmed Riboli Family Vineyard in the famous Napa Valley since 1968. The wine has that unmistakable character known as “Rutherford dust,” and its powerful tannins lead to a long-reaching finish. This classic intensely flavored Napa Valley Cabernet is beautifully balanced and will provide years of enjoyment. Sustainability is our top priority. Our Napa Valley vineyard is certified sustainable by CSWA.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Imperiale Prosecco Rose DOC Sparkling Rose Wine 750 ml

Drink it on its own or mix it into a cocktail. It’s the most fun you’ve ever had x10.

namePublicLong: Juicy Sparkle Blueberry Sparkling White Wine 2Pk/250 ml
namePublicShort: An unpretentious spin on Italian Prosecco, Juicy Sparkle is semi-sweet, full-sparkling, and packed with delicious flavor. Part of what makes it so special? Its fine, fizzy bubbles—a natural effect of the grape fermentation process. Juicy Sparkle Blueberry has an electric-blue color and is made with real blueberries (seriously). Drink it on its own or mix it into a cocktail. It’s the most fun you’ve ever had

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Moscato d'Asti DOCG Semi-Sweet White Wine 375 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Moscato d'Asti DOCG Semi-Sweet White Wine is produced entirely of Muscat Canelli grapes from the region of Asti in Piedmont, Italy.  During fermentation process, the alcohol is created in tandem with the wine’s natural carbonation. Once the desired sweetness is achieved, the wine is centrifuged and bottled. Its natural acidity and low pH strike the perfect balance with the wine’s inherent sweetness. Serve chilled and enjoy.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Sparkling Cranberry Semi-Sweet Rose Wine 750ml
namePublicShort: Stellabrate® this Holiday Season with our NEW Stella Rosa® Sparkling Cranberry Rosé Wine. It’s the perfect combination of bubbles and that traditional cranberry taste of the holidays, without being too tart. This makes a beautiful addition to your holiday table and is an all-natural sparkling wine from the Asti region in Piedmont, Italy.

namePublicLong: Santo Stefano Lambrusco Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Santo Stefano is a tribute to Santo Cambianica and Stefano Riboli, two pioneers of the California wine industry. In 1917, Santo arrived from Italy and founded San Antonio Winery, Saint Anthony’s Winery. His nephew Stefano joined him in 1938. Together, they began a tradition of family winemaking that spans four generations and continues today. In 1986, Stefano and Maddalena Riboli began farming a small, 16-acre vineyard in the heart of Napa Valley’s Rutherford appellation. Located along the Silverado Trail, the site was chosen for its rich, clay-loam soils and gentle slope. Enticing aromas of vanilla and spice are followed by ripe flavors of blackberry, currant, and black cherry. The finish shows hints of bittersweet chocolate. Within each handcrafted bottle, we celebrate the achievements of our family and all the pioneers of the California wine industry.

namePublicLong: Bodega Sangria Semi-Sweet Red Wine 2Pk/250 ml
namePublicShort: Since 1917, San Antonio Winery has won numerous gold medals and international awards. Our family now spans four generations of winemaking tradition. In keeping with this tradition, Bodega de San Antonio Sangria Tradicional is a semi-sweet red sangria. This festive wine bursts with fresh orange, lemon, and lime characteristics which are balanced by bright acidity. This versatile, refreshing Sangria is made with 100% natural grapes, fermented naturally, and enhanced by delicious natural fruits. Serve either chilled or on the rock with fresh citrus wedges! Salud!

namePublicLong: San Antonio Classic Chianti Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: San Antonio Classic Chianti Wine is named after the patron saint, Saint Anthony. San Antonio Winery has crafted this fine with for nearly one century. We honor the family's traditional methods of winemaking in all of our classic blends. Since 1917, San Antonio winery has won numerous gold medals and international awards. Our family now spans four generations of winemaking tradition. In keeping with this tradition, Classic Chianti is a hearty red wine with lovely aromas of berries and plums.

namePublicShort: Rancho Soledad Vineyard is located near the original Soledad Mission, which was founded by the Spanish Franciscan priests in 1791. In the 1800’s, this area became part of the privately owned Ranchos of California. Today, Riboli family farms Riesling on this historic site where decomposed granite soils combine with the cool, windy climate of the Monterey Bay. The result is a crisp and refreshing white wine with characteristic mineral notes.

namePublicLong: Natura Malbec

namePublicLong: Natura Chardonnay

namePublicLong: Banfi Le Rime Pinot Grigio
namePublicShort: Banfi Le Rime Pinot Grigio is a delicious and approachable white wine that is easy to drink and pairs well with a variety of foods. It is a good choice for casual meals, outdoor gatherings, or simply as a refreshing aperitif.

namePublicLong: Pacific Rim Wicked Good Red
namePublicShort: Inky dark in color and bursting with juicy flavors of fresh, dark berries.

namePublicLong: Natura Sauvignon Blanc
namePublicShort: A fresh new-world Sauvignon Blanc. Racy and bright with citrus aromas and a touch of minerality.

namePublicLong: Centine Rosé
namePublicShort: Centine Rosé is a pale pink wine with hints of ripe cherries, tasty strawberries and a touch of fresh herbs.

namePublicLong: Castello Banfi Rosso di Montalcino
namePublicShort: A complex wine characterized by a great varietal expression. On the nose, aromas of blackberries and raspberry meet coffee and tobacco hints. In the mouth the structure is wide, harmonious and well balanced by the typical acidity of the vintage. Excellent and persistent finish on the palate.

namePublicLong: Centine Rosso
namePublicShort: This Toscana Rosso blends traditional Sangiovese with consumer favorites Cabernet Sauvignon and Merlot. A full-bodied wine that is soft and delicious with nice acidity.

namePublicLong: Natura Merlot
namePublicShort: An easygoing Merlot full of character. Luscious fruit with notes of cocoa and a hint of smokiness.

namePublicLong: Banfi Chianti Classico
namePublicShort: Banfi's Chianti Classico is a delicious and authentic expression of the Chianti region, with a rich and complex character that will delight your palate.

namePublicLong: Banfi La Pettegola Vermentino
namePublicShort: Straw yellow wine, with intense citrus and yellow peach hints accompanied by floral and sage notes. The full structure is well balanced by the freshness. Very persistent and fruity finish on the palate.

namePublicLong: Natura Rosé
namePublicShort: A sophisticated Rose of the softest pink hue, and delicious, fresh strawberry flavors. Perfectly balanced with beautiful acidity for a Rose that's endlessly versatile and guaranteed to overdeliver.

namePublicLong: Natura Cabernet Sauvignon
namePublicShort: A robust, ruby red Cabernet with dark fruit and a hint of vanilla. A well made Cabernet with great structure, an excellent value.

namePublicLong: Castello Banfi Brunello di Montalcino
namePublicShort: A rich and elegant Brunello, both in structure and in olfactory expression. Brilliant ruby red with garnet-colored reflections, on the nose the aroma is sweet and fruity, the hints of fresh red fruit stand out, which combine perfectly with the more complex notes of licorice and pipe tobacco. The structure is powerful, and the palate is pleasantly enveloped by a consistent tannic texture, well balanced by a pleasant acidity. Extremely persistent with excellent aging potential.

namePublicLong: Banfi Chianti Classico Riserva
namePublicShort: Deep ruby in color. Rich bouquet of cherries, plums, and iris. Deep cherry and leather flavors with subtle wood notes. Supple tannins, good acidity, and a lingering finish.

namePublicLong: Castello Banfi Poggio Alle Mura Brunello di Montalcino
namePublicShort: The Castello Banfi Poggio Alle Mura Brunello di Montalcino is wine of exceptional quality and character, which showcases the best of what Montalcino has to offer. This wine has excellent aging potential and can be enjoyed for up to 20 years after bottling

namePublicLong: Rainstorm Pinot Noir
namePublicShort: Medium ruby red with a bouquet of strawberry, rose hip and cranberry. Rainstorm Pinot Noir is soft and elegant with flavors of bright cherry, pomegranate and red berries

namePublicLong: Natura Chardonnay
namePublicShort: Natura Chardonnay is a well-crafted and versatile wine that pairs well with seafood, poultry, and light pasta dishes. It is a great option for those who enjoy a fresh and fruity Chardonnay without the heavy oak influence.

namePublicLong: Natura Pinot Noir
namePublicShort: A Pinot Noir that is light, bright and delightful. This wine is organic, made from grapes grown without the use of chemical fertilizers, pesticides, or herbicides. It pairs well with grilled meats, roasted vegetables, and cheese.

namePublicLong: Centine Pinot Grigio
namePublicShort: Everyday Italian at it’s best, from Banfi . This Tuscan expression of Pinot Grigio is fresh, lively and delicious.

namePublicLong: Banfi Chianti Superiore
namePublicShort:
Intense ruby in color with shades of violet. A fruit-forward bouquet with some floral notes. Round and well balanced with 
black-cherry flavors and hints of spice. Well structured with good acidity, long and lingering finish.

namePublicLong: Banfi Principessa Gavia Gavi
namePublicShort: Banfi Principessa Gavia Gavi is a classic expression of the Gavi appellation and a testament to Banfi’s commitment to producing high-quality wines. It is a perfect example of a wine that embodies the Italian winemaking tradition, with its fresh, lively character and crisp, clean flavors.

namePublicLong: Banfi Col di Sasso
namePublicShort: Ruby red, with purple hues. Black cherry and spice aromas. Rich taste with soft tannins, delivering persistent black-fruit flavors and subtle hints of smoke, with a lingering finish.

namePublicLong: Natura Cabernet Sauvignon
namePublicShort: A robust, ruby red Cabernet with dark fruit and a hint of vanilla. A well made Cabernet with great structure, an excellent value.

namePublicLong: To create Stella Rosa Wines, the Riboli family chose the region of Asti, a province in Piedmont, Italy, as the source for its aromatic grapes, which have become the hallmark for the Stella Rosa style of wines. The area of Asti has particular significance to the family, as it is the birthplace of the family matriarch, Maddalena Riboli. The first Stella Rosa was Moscato D’Asti, which has become a flagship of the brand. Soon after, Stella Rosa Rosso was created – the brand’s first semi-sweet, semi-sparkling red wine blend, and first wine of its kind to be brought to America from Asti. The rapid phenomenal successes of these two wines began the lineage of Stella Rosa, which now boasts over 35 distinctive flavors.
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Semi-Sweet Red Wine is a proprietary blend of several red grape varietals including Brachetto. The wine is then combined with all-natural flavors of strawberry and red berry and flavors of blackberries, blueberries, and raspberries to create a delicious and refreshing experience. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: Urlar New Zealand  Pinot Noir Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Urlar Pinot Noir boasts enticing, dark, smoky cherry aromas and a lovely, almost saline note to the long palate, along with fine tension, freshness and good tannins. Crushed raspberry puree, black cherry and cranberry flavors have a terrific presence, with fresh and juicy details, including dragon-well tea, white pepper and forest floor, plus notes of clove and spice that linger on the finish. This is a fantastic natural and organic wine from Wairarapa that is produced using biodynamic farming practices.

namePublicLong: J. Lohr Hilltop Cabernet Sauvignon
namePublicShort: One of Paso Robles’ iconic, best known Cabernets, drawing from some of our top vineyard blocks. A small portion of Petit Verdot and Cabernet Franc provide additional complexity. Aged 18 months in French oak. Dense in structure, with layered, medium-weight tannins.

namePublicLong: J. Lohr Pure Paso Proprietary Red Wine
namePublicShort: J. Lohr Pure Paso artfully blends Cabernet Sauvignon and Petite Sirah - two J. Lohr benchmark varieties - into a unique proprietary red wine. The two varieties have long been intertwined in J. Lohr's winegrowing history and, in particular, the Lohr family's pioneering efforts in the Paso Robles region.

namePublicLong: J. Lohr Estates Seven Oaks Cabernet Sauvignon
namePublicShort: The J. Lohr Estates Seven Oaks Cabernet Sauvignon is dense and dark at the core. Ripe fruit aromas of black cherry and currant are accented by notes of toasted pastry, hazelnut, and vanilla from our extensive barrel aging program. Big, juicy red-fruit flavors infuse the palate while softly textured tannins lead to a long, gratifying finish.

To create Stella Rosa Wines, the Riboli family chose the region of Asti, a province in Piedmont, Italy, as the source for its aromatic grapes, which have become the hallmark for the Stella Rosa style of wines. The area of Asti has particular significance to the family, as it is the birthplace of the family matriarch, Maddalena Riboli. The first Stella Rosa was Moscato D’Asti, which has become a flagship of the brand. Soon after, Stella Rosa Rosso was created – the brand’s first semi-sweet, semi-sparkling red wine blend, and first wine of its kind to be brought to America from Asti. The rapid phenomenal successes of these two wines began the lineage of Stella Rosa, which now boasts over 35 distinctive flavors.
namePublicShort:
Stella Rosa Semi-Sparkling Ruby Rosé Grapefruit Red Wineis a proprietary blend of several white grape varietals including malvasia, moscato, and a touch of barbera for color. The wine has natural flavors of grapefruit that are created using a distillation process of Italian grapefruits grown in southern Italy. Its natural
acidity and low pH strike the perfect balance with the wine’s inherent sweetness. It is not cloying or heavy. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicShort: Urlar Sauvignon Blanc boasts flavors of honeydew melon and stone fruit with a crisp finish, a hallmark of New Zealand Sauvignon Blancs. A name meaning, in its very essence, “of the earth,” family-owned Urlar wines reflect the aromatic nature of their New Zealand origins. This natural and organic wine is produced using biodynamic farming practices to create a fresh and balanced end product of the highest quality.

namePublicLong: Kinderwood Monterey Chardonnay White Wine 750 ml

namePublicLong: Kinderwood Paso Robles Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Kinderwood Cabernet Sauvignon originates from the California Coastal region. Fermented in temperature-controlled tanks, it boasts vibrant fruitiness and crisp aromas. Barrel aging adds vanilla and spice nuances. The wine presents dark violet tones, wild berry aromas, and flavors of black cherry and raspberry, rounded off with soft tannins and a smooth finish.

namePublicLong: Nomine-Renard Brut Rose Champagne Sparkling Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Nomine-Renard Brut Rosé  is a blend of 45% Chardonnay, 45% Pinot Meunier, 10% Pinot Noir 75% of wine from 18 months old and 25% of reserve wine 6 villages in 3 different areas Les Coteaux du Petit Morin, Côte de Sézanne and Vallée de la Marne : Villevenard, Etoges, Broyes, Allemant, Charly sur Marne, Passy Grigny. Within a vineyard with an average age of 35 years old, the oldest plots of Pinot Noir are dedicated to produce our red wine. A high proportion of Chardonnay gives the Brut Rosé sensuality and elegance. Intense red fruit aromas, a hint of cherry & fresh grapefruit, followed by a subtle velvety mouthful. Perfect with spicy dishes with ginger, anise or citrus notes, salty sweet dishes or a fresh fruit salad.

namePublicLong: Nomine-Renard Blanc de Blancs Champagne Sparkling Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Nomine-Renard Blanc de Blancs is a chardonnay made from 65% of wine from 4 years old and 35% of reserve wine blended from the 5 previous vintages. It is comprised of grapes grown in 3 villages in the heart of les coteaux du petit Morin and la côte de Sézanne: Etoges, Villevenard, Allemant, from 20 to 45 years old plots. Nomine-Renard Blanc de Blancs features aromas of brioche, honey with notes of fresh wild flowers. The minerality and complexity give to this wine a 10 years cellaring potential. This wine pairs beautifully with scallops carpaccio with citrus sauce, roasted bass with fennel and herbs or simply served with warm pastries during an appetizer.

namePublicLong: Nomine-Renard Brut Champagne Sparkling Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Nomine-Renard Brut is a blend of 40% Chardonnay, 30% Pinot Noir and 30% Pinot Meunier. 75% of wine from 3 years old and 25% of reserve wine. From the youngest to the oldest plots up to 70 years old, the average age of our vineyard is 35 years old. Fresh and elegant with lots of minerality and citrus fruit aromas. Ideal for aperitif or to combine with fresh fish or smoked salmon.

namePublicShort: Enjoy Kenwood Vineyards Six Ridges Cabernet Sauvignon. We have carefully selected the top vineyards and best varietals in Alexander Valley, Dry Creek Valley, Russian River Valley, Sonoma Valley and Sonoma Coast to ensure each wine is the ultimate expression of the variety and terroir.

namePublicLong: Kenwood Vineyards Jack London Cabernet Sauvignon Vintage 2016 750mL, 29 Proof
namePublicShort: Enjoy Kenwood Vineyards Jack London Cabernet Sauvignon, a full bodied style with rich, well structured tannins, an elegant mouthfeel and a long finish.

namePublicLong: G.H.Mumm Grand Cordon Champagne 750mL, 12% ABV
namePublicShort: Embodying a passionate personality, G.H.Mumm Grand Cordon Rosé expresses its intense, fruity character with rich aromas of wild red and black berries, typical of the Pinot Noir grape variety cultivated in Maison Mumm’s legendary vineyards in the Champagne region of France.

namePublicLong: Jacob's Creek Classic Merlot Red Wine 1.5L, 14% ABV
namePublicShort: A modern Australian Classic – showcasing merlot's varietal purity with a soft, enjoyable finish. It has great lift with concentration of varietal spice and savory red fruits. This red wine is medium bodied with dried cranberry and ripe strawberry juiciness that flows generously into plush tannins.

namePublicLong: Kenwood Vineyards Six Ridges Chardonnay 750mL, 27 Proof
namePublicShort: Enjoy Kenwood Vineyards Six Ridges Chardonnay, which pairs beautifully with dishes like pan seared halibut with herb butter, risotto with spring vegetables, or sauteed chicken with wild rice.

namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Peach Semi-Sweet White Wine is a proprietary blend primarily from the Moscato grape with various other varietals. The wine is then combined with all-natural flavors of peach to create a delicious and refreshing experience. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all-natural, fruit-forward cocktail. 91 point Gold Medal Winner and Best Buy on Tastings.com!

namePublicLong: Santo Stefano Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Santo Stefano is a tribute to Santo Cambianica and Stefano Riboli, two pioneers of the California wine industry. In 1917, Santo arrived from Italy and founded San Antonio Winery, Saint Anthony’s Winery. His nephew Stefano joined him in 1938. Together, they began a tradition of family winemaking that spans four generations and continues today. In 1986, Stefano and Maddalena Riboli began farming a small, 16-acre vineyard in the heart of Napa Valley’s Rutherford appellation. Located along the Silverado Trail, the site was chosen for its rich, clay-loam soils and gentle slope. Enticing aromas of vanilla and spice are followed by ripe flavors of blackberry, currant, and black cherry. The finish shows hints of bittersweet chocolate. Within each handcrafted bottle, we celebrate the achievements of our family and all the pioneers of the California wine industry.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Black Semi-Sweet Red Wine 250 ml

Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: Nomine-Renard Brut Rosé Champagne Sparkling Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Nomine-Renard Brut Rose is a blend of 45% Chardonnay, 45% Pinot Meunier, 10% Pinot Noir 75% of wine from 18 months old and 25% of reserve wine 6 villages in 3 different areas Les Coteaux du Petit Morin, Côte de Sézanne and Vallée de la Marne : Villevenard, Etoges, Broyes, Allemant, Charly sur Marne, Passy Grigny. Within a vineyard with an average age of 35 years old, the oldest plots of Pinot Noir are dedicated to produce our red wine. A high proportion of Chardonnay gives the Brut Rosé sensuality and elegance. Intense red fruit aromas, a hint of cherry & fresh grapefruit, followed by a subtle velvety mouthful. Perfect with spicy dishes with ginger, anise or citrus notes, salty sweet dishes or a fresh fruit salad.

namePublicLong: Nomine-Renard Brut Champagne Sparkling Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Nomine-Renard Brut is a blend of 40% Chardonnay, 30% Pinot Noir and 30% Pinot Meunier. 75% of wine from 3 years old and 25% of reserve wine. From the youngest to the oldest plots up to 70 years old, the average age of our vineyard is 35 years old. Fresh and elegant with lots of minerality and citrus fruit aromas. Ideal for aperitif or to combine with fresh fish or smoked salmon.

namePublicLong: To create Stella Rosa Wines, the Riboli family chose the region of Asti, a province in Piedmont, Italy, as the source for its aromatic grapes, which have become the hallmark for the Stella Rosa style of wines. The area of Asti has particular significance to the family, as it is the birthplace of the family matriarch, Maddalena Riboli. The first Stella Rosa was Moscato D’Asti, which has become a flagship of the brand. Soon after, Stella Rosa Rosso was created – the brand’s first semi-sweet, semi-sparkling red wine blend, and first wine of its kind to be brought to America from Asti. The rapid phenomenal successes of these two wines began the lineage of Stella Rosa, which now boasts over 35 distinctive flavors.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Black Semi-Sweet Red Wine (4 Pack) 250 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Black Semi-Sweet Red Wine is a proprietary blend of several Italian red grape varietals including Brachetto. The wine is then combined with all-natural flavors of ripe blackberry, blueberry, and raspberry to create a delicious and refreshing experience. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all-natural, fruit-forward cocktail. 90 point Gold Medal Winner on Tastings.com!

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Tropical Passion and Mango Semi-Sweet White Wine Direct 750 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Tropical Passion and Mango Semi-Sweet White Wine is a propriety blend produced primarily from the Muscat Canelli grape with other varietals. The wine is combined with natural flavors of ripe mango and exotic passion fruit. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all natural, fruit-forward cocktail. 90 points Gold Medal Winner and Best Buy on Tastings.com

namePublicLong: Three Pines Paso Robles Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: The Italian term for Three Pines is "tre pini," which denotes the three pine trees that overlook San Antonio Winery's vineyard in Paso Robles. Three Pines is fashioned by the historical San Antonio Winery, founded over 100 years ago in downtown Los Angeles. Our selection is a blend of 30% Merlot, 25% each of Cabernet Sauvignon and Syrah, and 20% Petite Sirah. All of the flavors in our luscious selection coalesce into one united front.

namePublicLong: Three Pines Cardinal Red Sweet Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: The Italian term for Three Pines is "tre pini," which denotes the three pine trees that overlook San Antonio Winery's vineyard in Paso Robles. Three Pines is fashioned by the historical San Antonio Winery, founded over 100 years ago in downtown Los Angeles. It is the last producing Winery in L.A., and continues to hand craft wines from their estate vineyards in the Napa Valley, Monterey, Paso Robles and many viticulturally areas throughout California. Our selection is a blend of 30% Merlot, 25% each of Cabernet Sauvignon and Syrah, and 20% Petite Sirah. We are seeing more blends such as this, as winemakers and consumers finally agree that each grape adds its own special attributes and contribute to a greater whole. All of the flavors in our luscious selection coalesce into one united front.

The wine has natural flavors of grapefruit that are created using a distillation process of Italian grapefruits grown in southern Italy. Its natural acidity and low pH strike the perfect balance with the wine’s inherent sweetness. Serve chilled by the glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all-natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

Its natural acidity and low pH strike the perfect balance with the wine’s inherent sweetness. It is not cloying or heavy. namePublicLong: Nomine-Renard Brut Champagne Sparkling Wine 1.5L
namePublicShort: Nomine-Renard Brut is a blend of 40% Chardonnay, 30% Pinot Noir and 30% Pinot Meunier. 75% of wine from 3 years old and 25% of reserve wine. From the youngest to the oldest plots up to 70 years old, the average age of our vineyard is 35 years old. Fresh and elegant with lots of minerality and citrus fruit aromas. Ideal for aperitif or to combine with fresh fish or smoked salmon.

Stella Rosa Pink Semi-Sweet Rosé Wine is a propriety blend produced primarily from the Moscato grape with various other varietals. This blend results in a vibrant pink characteristic and flavors of strawberry and rose petals.Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite
spirit for an all natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Imperiale Prosecco DOC Sparkling White Wine 2Pk/187 ml
namePublicShort: The northeastern province of Veneto is home to Stella Rosa Prosecco DOC, a high-quality sparkler with a hint of sweetness. The prized Glera grapes are selected from specific familycultivated vineyards in the hills of Treviso. Its natural acidity and low pH strike the perfect balance with the wine’s inherent sweetness. It is not cloying or heavy. Serve chilled by-the-glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Watermelon Semi-Sweet Rose Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Watermelon Semi-Sweet Rose Wine is a proprietary blend of several white grape varietals including White Moscato (an indigenous grape variety from Piedmont), and a touch of barbera for color. The wine has natural flavors of watermelon that are created using a distillation process of Italian fruits grown in southern Italy. Serve chilled by the glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all-natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: Highlands 41 Monterey Chardonnay White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: The Highlands 41 Chardonnay White Wine comes from two estate vineyards in the Monterey appellation, Rancho Soledad and Loma Vista. Monterey is known for an extremely cool climate, with morning fog and afternoon breezes that allow for full development of ripe fruit flavors alongside the preservation of balanced acidity. This refreshing wine shows beautiful flavors of tropical fruit, grapefruit and zesty lime. With a spicy mid palate and a touch of minerality, the wine’s natural acidity brings it to a crisp, cool, satisfying finish.

namePublicLong: Maddalena Paso Robles Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Maddalena Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine comes from the best lots that our estate vineyards have to offer. The wines are matured in a selection of hand-crafted French and American oak barrels. Maddalena Cabernet Sauvignon shows ripe red fruit, including raspberry, plum, and spicy black cherry. Barrel aging contributes notes of vanilla, caramel, and oak spice. Maddalena Cabernet Sauvignon is extremely food friendly, our Cabernet Sauvignon pairs well with a range of dishes. Enjoy with grilled steaks as well as hearty pastas.  Our Paso Robles vineyard is certified sustainable by CSWA.

namePublicLong: Maddalena Monterey Riesling White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: In creating Maddalena Riesling, the alcoholic fermentation is stopped before the yeast has converted all the natural grape sugar into alcohol. In doing so, this arrested fermentation allows the natural sweetness of the wine to be maintained. Maddalena Riesling reveals aromas of apricot, honey, and wildflowers. The rich mouth greets the palate with fresh fruit flavors of pear and green apple. Quality begins in the vineyards. The Riboli Family established estate vineyards in Paso Robles in order to ensure the ultimate level of grape quality. Fully mature grapes concentrate ripe flavors and aromas. Our Paso Robles and Monterey vineyards are certified sustainable by CSWA.

namePublicLong: Highlands 41 Paso Robles Black Granite Red Blend Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: The Highlands 41 Black Granite Red Wine is a fascinating blend of red varietals sourced from our estate vineyards in Paso Robles. Zinfandel and Petite Sirah form the foundation of this wine, grown in our Creston Highlands Vineyard located in the rolling hills of the northeastern section of the Creston District AVA. With bright color and high fruit intensity, our Black Granite shows lively flavors of raspberry, blackberry and plum with warm notes of spice, brown sugar and vanilla. This is an approachable, well-integrated wine with long, soft tannins and a smooth finish.

namePublicLong: Highlands 41 Paso Robles Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Highlands 41 Cabernet Sauvignon  is a single vineyard wine from our Creston Highlands Vineyard in the Paso Robles appellation. Aged in small oak barrels for 10 months, this deeply colored Cabernet Sauvignon exhibits a fountain of blueberry, blackberry and other mature fruits that give the wine a rich, concentrated mouthfeel. Round on the mid-palate, the wine has soft, well-integrated tannins, balanced acidity and a spicy finish that lasts and lasts. Paso Robles winery solar panels provide 100% of the needed electricity, and wastewater is effectively reclaimed and recycled for additional uses.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Organic Orange Fusion Semi-Sweet White Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: Stella Rosa Organic Orange Fusion Semi-Sweet White Wine is a proprietary blend of organic white grape varietals from Piedmont, Italy. The wine’s natural flavor is light, elegant and fresh. The trio of orange varieties are combined with other fruits for balance and a rich taste. The grapes are harvested, pressed, centrifuged, and then cold stored as juice at 28 degrees Fahrenheit. The juice is fermented at various intervals throughout the year, allowing the wine to remain fresh and delicate. Serve chilled by the glass, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit for an all-natural, fruit-forward cocktail.

namePublicLong: Stella Rosa Pineapple Chili White Wine 750ml
namePublicShort: Spice up your next party with our new Stella Rosa Pineapple Chili White Wine. This semi-sweet, semi-sparkling wine is made with a proprietary blend of primarily the Moscato d’Asti grape with natural flavors of ripe tropical pineapple and spicy chili. This bold flavor is sure to impress. Serve chilled, pour over ice, or mix with your favorite spirit in a cocktail.

namePublicLong: La Quinta Syrah Port Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: La Quinta Syrah Port is considered a ruby port due to its dark red color. Paso Robles provides an ideal climate for the ripening of Syrah grapes to 25-27º Brix. Each variety is then harvested and fermented separately. At approximately 8-10º Brix, California brandy is added to arrest the fermentation.

namePublicLong: San Simeon Paso Robles Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: San Simeon Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon Red Wine was aged in a selection of 78% new French and American Oak barrels. This is a high intensity Cabernet with bright color and robust flavors of blackberry, plum and black cherry with a satisfying with a long, round finish. Sustainability is a top priority at San Simeon. Our Paso Robles Vineyards are certified sustainable by the rigorous California Sustainable Wine Alliance (CSWA).

namePublicLong: San Antonio Specialty Imperial Red Semi-Sweet Red Wine 750ml
namePublicShort: San Antonio Specialty Imperial is a semi-sweet red wine crafted from Ruby Cabernet grapes with aromas of plum and cherries. The bold flavors combine to create a semi-sweet taste with notes of red berry. Enjoy this wine with a variety of appetizers and entrees, such as cheese, fresh fruit and red meat. Serve slightly chilled.

namePublicLong: Opaque Paso Robles Zinfandel Red Wine 750 ml
namePublicShort: The word ‘opaque’ means “impenetrable to light” and refers to the dark, inky color of our family’s Zinfandel. Originally from Croatia, Zinfandel is now mainly planted in California and Italy. In Italy, Zinfandel is known as Primitivo. Our estate vineyard in Paso Robles is named Quarry Heights due to its steep, rocky hillsides and view of an old quarry. After aging in French oak barrels for 18 months, our Zinfandel reveals ripe flavors of blackberry, boysenberry, and black cherry with accents of spice and dark cocoa. Enjoy the darkness!
